---
description: These rules apply when developing frontend components using Streamlit.
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use Streamlit's imperative API for building UIs (e.g., st.title, st.button, st.dataframe).
- Manage state with st.session_state to persist data across reruns.
- Organize Streamlit apps in separate .py files under a 'streamlit/' directory or similar.
- Always add type hints to functions and variables, e.g., def main() -> None:
- Use caching with @st.cache_data or @st.cache_resource for performance-critical functions.
- Handle errors gracefully, using st.error for user-facing messages.
- Ensure compatibility with Python 3.11+ features where applicable.
